Re: explanation for 徹底
by Hyperworm » Tue 08.30.2011 10:02 am So Just Throw A Chair At Me wrote:"a certain rule enforced in the village"?More like it.This is 徹底した + ある掟.したある doesn't exist as a verb construction (not to be confused with してある).Incidentally, what's going on with the verb at the end of the OP's sentence...? >_>;
